HEADWORD: Euxenite
<hw>Eux"e*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
hospitable. So named because it contains a number of rare
elements.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A brownish black mineral with a
metallic luster, found in Norway. It contains niobium, titanium,
yttrium, and uranium, with some other metals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

